# Responsive Design — Always Enforce

This project must work correctly on **mobile (≥320px)**, **tablet (≥768px)**, and **desktop (≥1280px)**. Every `.tsx` file you touch must pass the checklist below before you finish.

---

## Breakpoint Reference (Tailwind)

| Prefix | Min-width | Target device |
|--------|-----------|---------------|
| *(none)* | 0px | Mobile (base, always start here) |
| `sm:` | 640px | Large phone / small tablet |
| `md:` | 768px | Tablet |
| `lg:` | 1024px | Small laptop |
| `xl:` | 1280px | Desktop |

---

## Rules

### 1 — Mobile-first: base classes target mobile, breakpoint prefixes opt-in to larger screens

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — stacks on mobile, side-by-side on tablet+
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">

// ❌ WRONG — only works on desktop
<div className="flex flex-row gap-4">
```

### 2 — Never use fixed pixel widths for containers or layout elements

```tsx
// ✅
<div className="w-full max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4">

// ❌
<div style={{ width: '1200px' }}>
<div className="w-[1200px]">
```

### 3 — Grids must be responsive

```tsx
// ✅
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">

// ❌
<div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-4">
```

### 4 — Text must scale down on small screens

```tsx
// ✅
<h1 className="text-xl md:text-3xl font-bold">

// ❌
<h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">
```

### 5 — Padding/margin must reduce on mobile

```tsx
// ✅
<div className="px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-12 py-4 md:py-8">

// ❌
<div className="px-12 py-8">
```

### 6 — Sidebar and nav must collapse or hide on mobile

```tsx
// ✅ — hide on mobile, show on desktop
<aside className="hidden lg:flex lg:flex-col w-64 ...">

// ✅ — toggle-based mobile drawer (overlay)
<aside className={`fixed inset-y-0 left-0 z-40 w-64 lg:static lg:block ${open ? 'block' : 'hidden'}`}>
```

### 7 — Tables must scroll horizontally on mobile, never overflow the viewport

```tsx
// ✅
<div className="overflow-x-auto w-full">
  <table className="min-w-full ...">

// ❌
<table className="w-full ...">  {/* no scroll wrapper */}
```

### 8 — Modals must be full-screen or near-full on mobile

```tsx
// ✅
<div className="w-full max-w-lg mx-4 md:mx-auto rounded-2xl ...">

// ❌
<div className="w-[560px] rounded-2xl ...">
```

### 9 — Touch targets must be ≥44px tall on mobile

```tsx
// ✅
<button className="h-11 px-4 ...">

// ❌
<button className="h-6 px-2 ...">
```

### 10 — Overflow must be controlled — never let content spill horizontally

```tsx
// ✅ — truncate long text
<p className="truncate max-w-xs">

// ✅ — allow wrapping
<p className="break-words">

// ❌ — can overflow on mobile
<p className="whitespace-nowrap">  {/* without overflow-x-auto parent */}
```

---

## Audit Checklist — Run on Every File You Touch

Before finishing any edit, check each of these:

- [ ] No fixed-pixel widths on layout containers
- [ ] All grids use `grid-cols-1` as the mobile base
- [ ] All `flex-row` have a mobile fallback (`flex-col` on base)
- [ ] Padding / margin scales down on mobile (`px-4 md:px-8`)
- [ ] Text sizes scale down on mobile (`text-base md:text-xl`)
- [ ] Tables wrapped in `overflow-x-auto`
- [ ] Modals use `w-full max-w-X` not fixed widths
- [ ] All buttons / interactive elements are `h-11` or taller on mobile
- [ ] Sidebars hidden or collapsible on mobile (`hidden lg:flex`)
- [ ] No `whitespace-nowrap` without an `overflow-x-auto` ancestor

---

## When You Spot a Violation

Fix it immediately — do not leave it in place. Apply the mobile-first Tailwind pattern from the examples above. If a layout needs significant restructuring (e.g., a sidebar drawer), add the `lg:hidden` hamburger button and overlay panel in the same edit.
